<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6324] DatabaseMetaData.getJDBCMinorVersion() should return 2 now that we&apos;ve implemented JDBC 4.2</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6324</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Now that the work on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6000&quot; title=&quot;Implement support for JDBC 4.2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-6000&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-6000&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is done, DatabaseMetaData.getJDBCMinorVersion() should return 2 rather than 1. The following script shows that we&apos;re still returning 1:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;connect &apos;jdbc:derby:memory:db;create=true&apos;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;call syscs_util.syscs_register_tool( &apos;databaseMetaData&apos;, true );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;values getJDBCMajorVersion();&lt;br/&gt;
values getJDBCMinorVersion();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;call syscs_util.syscs_register_tool( &apos;databaseMetaData&apos;, false );&lt;/p&gt;</description>
